word_mean_info__list.difference: 较正式用词，侧重已经开始，且希望完成，但常隐含着不一定有预期的结果。
和endeavour一样，表示付出巨大努力，但strive侧重劳累与紧张，而不强调努力的结果。
正式用词，指尽最大努力、认真地克服困难去做某事。
普通用词，可与attempt换用，但强调努力或尝试，后跟不定式表示努力或争取；后跟动名词表示尝试。
普通用词，含义广，指用科学方法对某物质进行测试以估价其性质或效能等。
多指用科学方法在实验室内进行较系统的操作实验以验证、解释或说明某一理论、定理或某一观点等。
指为观察、研究某事物以区别其真伪、优劣或效果等而进行较长时间的试验或试用过程。
普通用词，多用于口语或非正式场合，指试一试。

bilingual.source: Do you try to behave this way?
Which would you most like to try?
Try to look on the bright side.
bilingual.target: 尝试看到事情好的一面。

list.abstract: 《Try》是美国流行女歌手Colbie Caillat演唱的一首英语流行歌曲，Colbie Caillat、Antonio Dixon、Kenneth "Babyface" Edmonds、Jason Reeves作词作曲，2014年6月9日发行，收录在专辑《Gypsy Heart Side A》。
try，是青春女子三人组合组成的乐队，2006年成立，乐队主要成员是：林可昕、王奕心、沈丹丹三人。2006年12月27日，try首张音乐大碟《勇敢的女孩》全亚洲发行，主打歌《不要在我寂寞的时候说爱我》获得中国移动百度手机彩铃排行榜热门金曲第一位。try乐队以原创音乐为基础，结合靓丽的外型和动感时尚的舞蹈，以组合的方式全方位的展现音乐艺术的魅力。

yingyinNormal.en: It's time I try something new.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是时候我尝试一些新的东西。

yingyinNormal.en: Let's try something a little more challenging.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们尝试更具挑战性的。

yingyinNormal.en: It is common sense to take a method and try it. And if it fails, admit it frankly and try another. But above all, try something.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想办法试一试很正常，如果失败了，坦白承认，然后重新来过，但重要的是要尝试。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah but, you don't want to try to much too fast. You know? I mean, you do remember what happened to the little girl that tried to much too fast don't you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 但你也别一下子做太多尝试，你记得那个，一下子做太多尝试的小女孩吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, we are ready to try anything. Okay, there's an herbal tea you can drink. Okay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们愿意尝试任何事。你可以喝一种药草茶。

yingyinNormal.en: You need to listen to what she says. Try to see the forest through her eyes.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你得仔细聆听她所说的话，尝试透过她的眼睛看森林。

yingyinNormal.en: But you must try, Master. With every passing day we become less human.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但你必须尝试，掌握。日子一天天过去我们越来越不像人。

yingyinNormal.en: So I yes, I was the kind of opposite of Bill Clinton who tried marijuana but didn't inhale. See, I didn't try marijuana but I did inhale.
yingyinNormal.zh: 于是我正好是比尔·克林顿的反面，他尝试过大麻，但没有吸入，而我呢，明白吗，我没有尝试，但吸入了。

yingyinNormal.en: And when you're done, you try my job. You don't like it, you walk away.
yingyinNormal.zh: 完事之后，你尝试一下我的工作，如果不喜欢，可以走人。

yingyinNormal.en: But don't try to sneak it all in one day. Drinking too much water can actually be dangerous.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但别尝试在一天之内完成，喝太多水其实很危险。

yingyinNormal.en: But above all, we must try something. Thank you, and God Bless the United States of America.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但重要的，是要尝试，谢谢，天佑美利坚合众国。

yingyinNormal.en: It is a relaxing place to enjoy the sunshine and try stand-up paddle boarding.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是一个放松好好享受阳光的地方，您可以尝试立桨冲浪。

yingyinNormal.en: Try this method. Step 1: Choose a day when waves are moderate, but regular.
yingyinNormal.zh: 请尝试以下方法，步骤一：选择海浪中等但比较规律的一天。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, try seeing accomplishment. Is there a difference? John, you haven't focused.
yingyinNormal.zh: 要去尝试看成果。有区别吗？约翰。你还没有集中你的精力。

yingyinNormal.en: The New Deal succeeded for many years, but we must now try something newer before it fails us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 新政成功了那么多年，但在新政失效前，我们得尝试更新的东西。

yingyinNormal.en: I give up. Riley, as much as I try, it's impossible to control what goes on all the time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我放弃了。莱丽，我尝试过很多次了，想要一直掌控一切是不可能的。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, Dad? Did you ever want to try something new, but were afraid of what your friends think?
yingyinNormal.zh: 嗨，爸爸？你曾否想要尝试全新的事物，却害怕朋友对你的看法吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Ma and I have decided that because we don't know what we like, we get to try everything.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我和妈妈决定了，因为我们不知道自己喜欢什么，所以就什么都尝试一下。

yingyinNormal.en: He doesn't dumb down his presentations, but he does try to limit each slide to one key idea.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他并没有使他的简报保持沉默，但是他也尝试每张投影片限制一个关键概念。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I'm just not sure I should still be a lawyer. I mean, maybe new Savi should try something new.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不确定自己是不是还应该当律师，或许新的萨维应该尝试一下别的工作。

sense_info_list.zh: 试图; 设法; 努力

examination_example.sentence: So when someone <highlight>tries</highlight> to communicate with you, just be in that communication wholeheartedly.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所以当有人试图和你交流时，要全心全意地投入进去。

examination_example.sentence: When I think of a sad memory, I do what everybody does — <highlight>try</highlight> to put it to one side.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我想起一段悲伤的回忆时，我会做每个人都会做的事——试着把它放在一边。

examination_example.sentence: No one <highlight>tries</highlight> harder than the jobless to find silver linings in this national economic disaster.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 没有人比失业者更努力地在这场国家经济灾难中寻找一线希望。

sense_info_list.en: do or use something in order to find out if you like it

examination_example.sentence: SilverSneakers offers them for older adults, or <highlight>try</highlight> EverWalk for virtual challenges.
examination_example.sentence_trans: SilverSneakers为老年人提供这些，或者尝试EverWalk的虚拟挑战。

examination_example.sentence: But Ashe and others argued that the "threatened" tag gave the federal government flexibility to <highlight>try</highlight> out new, potentially less confrontational conservation approaches.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但Ashe和其他人认为，“受威胁”的标签让联邦政府可以灵活地尝试新的、潜在对抗性较少的保护方法。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Try</highlight> a hair stylist instead of a barber.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尝试让发型师做头发，而不是理发师。

word_usage.usage: try to do sth.是设法、尽量去做某事，否定形式是try not to do sth.，try doing sth.尝试、试试做某事，带有建议的含义。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 常用词，意为“试图、尽力、设法”。
较正式，意为“试图、设法作一番努力”，后常与to连用。
正式用语，意为“努力，尽力(后接to)”，指为达到目标而做的一切努力。

examination_example.sentence: She <highlight>tries</highlight> to force people to accept her radical ideas.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她试图迫使人们接受她的激进观点。

examination_example.sentence: They are not <highlight>trying</highlight> to prove that the use of digital devices reduces young people's wellbeing .
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们并不是试图证明数字设备的使用会降低年轻人的幸福感。

examination_example.sentence: That won't stop inventors from dreaming up new ways to fly and <highlight>trying</highlight> to persuade investors to back their sometimes outrageous schemes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这不会阻止发明家们追求新飞行方式的梦想，他们还试图说服投资者支持那些有时看起来很离谱的计划。

sense_info_list.en: make an effort to do something

examination_example.sentence: They <highlight>try</highlight> hard to appear optimistic.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们努力表现得乐观。

examination_example.sentence: Schellenberg didn't tell his assistants what exactly he was <highlight>trying</highlight> to prove.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Schellenberg没有告诉他的助手他到底想努力证明什么。

examination_example.sentence: Macy's has been moving aggressively to <highlight>try</highlight> to remake itself for a new era of shopping.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 梅西百货一直在积极努力试图重塑自己以迎接新的购物时代。

word_usage.usage:
try to do和try doing的区别：
try to do: 设法或努力去做，强调动作，但结果不一定成功，相当于“try one's best to do”；try doing: 试着做，抱着试试看的想法做。
示例：Tom tried to work out this difficult maths problem but failed, so he tried seeking another way.
汤姆努力解这道数学难题未果，因此他尝试寻找另一种方法。

examination_example.sentence: Scientists have <highlight>tried</highlight> to tap Intermesh donors, too, with mixed success.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 科学家们也曾尝试利用互联网捐助者，但结果喜忧参半。

examination_example.sentence: The world is dotted with futuristic, high-tech cities <highlight>trying</highlight> to attract the biggest international companies.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 世界各地都遍布着试图吸引最大跨国企业的未来派高科技城市。

examination_example.sentence: Have you thought about <highlight>trying</highlight> fresh juices in the morning?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你有在早上尝试饮用新鲜果汁吗？

examination_example.sentence: Scott agrees to <highlight>try</highlight> more fruit juices for the kids and to make real macaroni and cheese. Score one point for the doctor, zero for diabetes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 斯科特同意为孩子们尝试更多的果汁，并做真正的通心粉和奶酪。医生得一分，糖尿病的几率就为零。

examination_example.sentence: "I <highlight>try</highlight> to make things as inexpensive as possible," said Hunt, who uses free digital textbooks for his classes but designs his own curriculum.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 亨特说：“我试图尽可能降低成本。”他在课堂上使用免费的数字教科书，但他设计了自己的课程。

examination_example.sentence: It has been <highlight>trying</highlight> out monitoring stations that are intended to yield minute-to-minute maps of outdoor air pollution.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它一直在试行监测站，以绘制出每分钟的室外空气污染图。

examination_example.sentence: Only one representative, Jad Tabet from Lebanon, <highlight>tried</highlight> to raise the issue.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 只有黎巴嫩的一名代表 Jad Tabet 试图提出这个问题。

examination_example.sentence: They <highlight>tried</highlight> everything possible to escape from the cage.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们想尽一切办法逃出笼子。

examination_example.sentence: It can be hard to identify which parcels are carrying crucial items such as Social Security checks, but USPS and UPS <highlight>try</highlight> their best to prioritize sensitive ma trial.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 很难确定哪些包裹中携带着社会保险支票等重要物品，但美国邮政和联合包裹服务公司会尽最大努力优先处理敏感包裹。

examination_example.sentence: I've <highlight>tried</highlight>, but it seems like he just has no time for me.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我努力了，但他好像没时间陪我。

examination_example.sentence: He began studying them, <highlight>trying</highlight> to learn the differences between the birds and noticing their different behaviors.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他开始研究它们，试图了解鸟类之间的差异，并注意到它们不同的行为。

examination_example.sentence: Instead of <highlight>trying</highlight> to pick out a job for me, they helped me learn those things that led me to it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们没有试图为我挑选一份工作，而是帮助我学习那些有利于我找到工作的东西。

examination_example.sentence: You should give it a <highlight>try</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你应该试一下。

examination_example.sentence: Approaching the vehicle, they saw that a woman was <highlight>trying</highlight> to get out of the broken window.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们走近那辆车，看到一个女人正试图从破碎的窗户里出去。

word_usage.usage:
try后接to do或doing，所表达的意义不同，二者的区别是：
①try doing sth.意为“试着做某事”，即采取不同方式、方法尝试：
He tried writing to her but didn't receive her reply.
他试着给她写信，但是没收到她的回信。
②try to do sth.意思是“设法做某事”，常含有某种难度之意，不一定成功，未成事实：
He tried to write to her,but could not.
他设法给她写信，但没有写成。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: adj. 经证明有效的；经证明可靠的
n. 讯问；审讯；审理；考验；试验；测试；磨练；选拔赛；预赛
困难的；恼人的；难以忍受的

word_family.mean: v. 试；尝试；审讯；审判；用刨子刨平；加热以提取；熬；争取；调查

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 继续尝试；继续努力；坚持尝试
尽力做某事；努力做某事；试着做某事
尝试做某事；试着做某事

sense_info_list.en: make an effort to do something
sense_info_list.zh: 试图; 设法; 努力

examination_example.sentence: Some are <highlight>trying</highlight> to send messages of love and care in different ways.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有些人试图以不同的方式传递爱和关怀的信息。

examination_example.sentence: A lot of teens <highlight>try</highlight> not to lose the friendship once they become friends with some people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多青少年在与一些人成为朋友后努力不失去友谊。

examination_example.sentence: He would <highlight>try</highlight> his best to save his daughter.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他会尽力救他的女儿。

sense_info_list.en: do or use something in order to find out if you like it

examination_example.sentence: It is a chance to <highlight>try</highlight> new things.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是一个尝试新事物的机会。

examination_example.sentence: Keep <highlight>trying</highlight> and you'll make progress.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 继续努力，你会取得进步的。

examination_example.sentence: I <highlight>tried</highlight> many different ways of doing it, but none of  them were successful.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我尝试了许多不同的方法，但都没有成功。

word_usage.usage:
try to do和try doing的区别：
try to do: 设法或努力去做，强调动作，但结果不一定成功，相当于“try one's best to do”；try doing: 试着做，抱着试试看的想法做。
示例：Tom tried to work out this difficult maths problem but failed, so he tried seeking another way.
汤姆努力解这道数学难题未果，因此他尝试寻找另一种方法。
